Title: Privilege Escalation: Low Privilege User Can View Super Admin-Restricted Client User Data
Description: A low privilege user is able to access sensitive client user information, including login details, email addresses, and user profiles. These functionalities are part of the Client Management system, which should be restricted to Super Admins. This vulnerability allows unauthorized access to private client user data, which can lead to significant confidentiality breaches and data exposure.

Impact:

Exposure of sensitive client user data, including login credentials and personal information.
Potential for privacy violations and misuse of client information.
Risk of data disclosure, which can lead to unauthorized access or identity theft.
Recommendation:

Implement strict access control to ensure only authorized Super Admins can view and manage client user data.
Enforce role-based access control (RBAC) and perform thorough permission checks before displaying sensitive information.
Conduct regular security audits to ensure that lower privilege users do not have access to sensitive admin functionalities.
